---
import CaseStudy from '../../layouts/CaseStudy.astro';
---
<CaseStudy slug="triax">
  <Fragment slot="meta">
    <div class="cs-meta-card">
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Client</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Triax Technologies</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Duration</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Oct 2021 – Feb 2022</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Role</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Marketing Content Manager</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Industry</div><div class="cs-meta-value">B2B SaaS / IoT</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Prospects</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Hess · Shell</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-strip">
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">300%</div><div class="stat-label">Webinar attendance growth</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">2</div><div class="stat-label">Fortune 50 prospects advanced</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">5 mos</div><div class="stat-label">Marketing automation stood up</div></div>
    </div>
  </Fragment>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Context · Action · Result</div>
    <div class="car-grid">
      <div class="car-sidebar">
        <div class="car-step active" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-triax-1')"><div class="car-step-label">01 · Context</div><div class="car-step-title">The situation</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-triax-2')"><div class="car-step-label">02 · Action</div><div class="car-step-title">What I did</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-triax-3')"><div class="car-step-label">03 · Result</div><div class="car-step-title">What it produced</div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div id="car-triax-1" class="car-content">
          <div class="car-content-label">01 · Context</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Strong product. Broken messaging. Stalled enterprise pipeline.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Triax Technologies built SaaS and IoT solutions for industrial safety and operations, but the marketing system was not translating the product's value clearly enough for enterprise buyers. Messaging leaned heavily on technical IoT language, while the actual decision-makers — operations, safety, and executive stakeholders — needed clearer business outcomes.<br /><br />Webinars were drawing only 11 attendees, sales momentum had slowed, and enterprise prospects including Hess and Shell were aware of the product but not progressing fast enough. Salesforce and Pardot workflows were not yet operating as a structured demand-generation engine.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-triax-2" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">02 · Action</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Rebuilt the messaging system and stood up marketing automation.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Partnered with marketing and sales leadership to rebuild the content strategy around buyer clarity, not technical complexity. Rewrote messaging to translate SaaS and IoT capabilities into clearer business narratives for operational and executive stakeholders.<br /><br />Implemented Salesforce and Pardot workflows to support automated outreach, email marketing, and campaign execution. Redesigned the webinar program with stronger content structure, tighter promotion, and clearer audience targeting. Managed two junior marketers supporting execution through Salesforce and social channels.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-triax-3" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">03 · Result</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">300% webinar growth and Fortune 50 sales progression.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Webinar attendance grew from 11 to 35 to 55 attendees across three sessions — a 300% increase driven by stronger content, improved format, and more targeted promotion. Hess and Shell advanced into late-stage enterprise sales conversations through clearer messaging and more relevant campaign content.<br /><br />Within five months, Triax had a more usable messaging system, a working Salesforce/Pardot marketing automation foundation, and stronger content support for enterprise sales. The role ended when a new CEO arrived and laid off roughly one-third of the company across marketing, business development, sales, and HR.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</CaseStudy>
